<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1884" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1884">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/69.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Snyder</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that under
                            recent legislation, immigrants coming third class or as deck passengers
                            to Panama <pb facs="1388" n="1272" xml:id="pg_1272"/> are required to
                            deposit $30 with the Government pending presentation of proof that they
                            have obtained permanent work.</p>
                        <p>This law was passed, it is claimed, to avoid a possible future menace as
                            a result of the bad financial condition of the country and the number of
                            West Indians and others who have arrived lately and failed to obtain
                            work owing to the completion of the Canal.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Alban G. Snyder.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>